## Required workflow

1. Start with compact `{{extensionId}}_wiki_search({ query, limit: 5 })` for {{topicName}} issues.
2. Use `{{extensionId}}_wiki_sections({ page, maxSections })` when the right page is found but the relevant heading is unclear.
3. Prefer exact section extraction for final evidence:
   - `{{extensionId}}_wiki_extract({ page, section, maxChars: 4000-8000, maxSections: 3-6 })`
4. Use query extraction for exploration only, then switch to exact headings when available.
5. If query extraction over-selects broad sections, retry with `requireAllTerms: true` or `minTokenMatches`.
6. Use `{{extensionId}}_wiki_read` only when broad page context is needed or no relevant heading can be identified.
7. Use `{{extensionId}}_wiki_related` when the issue spans linked topics.
8. Use `{{extensionId}}_wiki_smoke_test` when validating parser, heading, or link fidelity.
9. Run read-only local diagnostics when system/project evidence is relevant.
10. Compare documentation guidance with observed local state.
11. Cite local paths and section names in final answers.
12. Ask before destructive or user-facing changes.

## Source priority

1. Local {{displayName}} corpus via `{{extensionId}}_wiki_*` tools.
2. Local project/system evidence relevant to the user's current environment.
3. Official online {{displayName}} documentation only when local docs are missing, stale, or insufficient.
4. Other sources only when necessary and clearly labeled.

## Tool usage

- `{{extensionId}}_wiki_search({ query, limit, includeSnippets, includeDetails })`: find candidate pages. Output is compact by default (`title`, `path`, `score`); request snippets/details only when needed.
- `{{extensionId}}_wiki_sections({ page, maxSections })`: inspect headings before extracting from large pages.
- `{{extensionId}}_wiki_extract({ page, section, maxChars, maxSections })`: retrieve focused exact sections; best for final answers.
- `{{extensionId}}_wiki_extract({ page, query, maxChars, maxSections, minTokenMatches, requireAllTerms })`: retrieve query-relevant sections; best for exploration, with stricter filters for broad queries.
- `{{extensionId}}_wiki_read({ page, maxChars })`: retrieve broad page text; use sparingly.
- `{{extensionId}}_wiki_related({ page, limit })`: discover linked local pages.
- `{{extensionId}}_wiki_smoke_test({ sampleSize })`: validate title/heading/link parser fidelity while tuning the package.

