## Token/output discipline

- Keep search limits small (`limit: 5-10`) unless exploring broadly.
- Keep search compact by default; set `includeSnippets` or `includeDetails` only when they improve selection confidence.
- Prefer `search -> sections -> exact section extract` for final answers.
- Use query extraction only to discover likely sections on large pages; use `requireAllTerms` or `minTokenMatches` when broad terms over-select.
- Use `maxChars` around 4000-8000 and `maxSections` around 3-6 for focused answers.
- Use `read` only when the relevant section cannot be identified.
- If a tool reports `omittedSectionCount`, `omittedLinkCount`, `queryFilter`, or `truncated: true`, mention it when it affects confidence.

## Citation format

Use local source citations like:

```txt
Sources:
- {{docsPath}}/Path/To/Page.md — Relevant section
- {{docsPath}}/Other/Page.html — Other section
```
